{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"[E2] Forge Author grant — GO (authorship preservation). Admin ACL read as JoeOakhartNava: rebar project sets no forgeAuthor locally, but inherits from All-Projects which grants 'forgeAuthor -> Registered Users' on refs/heads/* (also forgeCommitter -> Project-Owners). A push-for-review to refs/for/refs/heads/main is evaluated against refs/heads/* for forgeAuthor, so a Registered-User shepherd CAN push a git-am'd commit whose Author is the original contributor. => CONTRIBUTING shepherded-patch policy uses the git am authorship-preservation path (author=contributor, committer=shepherd), NOT the Co-authored-by fallback. No config change needed (grant already effective)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783649305149325001,"uuid":"954d9086-ecbb-40fd-8f80-159470ed278a"}